+ D2 Setup(Windows)
-   Download appropriate windows binary from https://github.com/terrastruct/d2/releases ex: d2-v0.7.1-windows-amd64.msi
-   Run the the binary
-   Add D2 to your path:
        ~ Window Start search environment variables
        ~ New variable
        ~ Name your variable and add the file path to the d2 executable ex: C:\Program Files\d2
        ~ Restart terminal
-   Test D2 was installed successfully:
        ~ In a terminal(Command prompt or powershell)
        ~ d2 --version
        ~ echo 'x -> y -> z' > in.d2
        ~ d2 -w input.d2 out.svg
-   Take the tour at https://d2lang.com/ to get familiar with the tool
